20/02/2007
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- US Ambassador to BiH Douglas McElhaney reiterated on Monday (February 19th) the importance of completing crucial BiH police reforms, in order to comply with EU requirements for a Stabilisation and Association Agreement. His comment followed a meeting with Republika Srpska (RS) Prime Minister Milorad Dodik in Banja Luka. RS has said it is unwilling to give up its entity police force. (Dnevni avaz, Nezavisne novine - 20/02/07; RTRS, Srna - 19/02/07)
